% parrot0 WORLD FACTS — curated category membership as KNOWLEDGE, not C literals.
%
% gen230 (LLMSCORE behavioural resemblance). An LLM trivially "names a color that
% starts with B"; parrot0 can too, the honest KB-first way — the members live here
% as facts, and mod_namestart (20-math.c) reads the category + the target initial
% and returns the first known member. Add a category_member fact and the capability
% extends for free; nothing is hardcoded in C.
%
% NB: geography (capitals) was intentionally NOT added here — the `capital`
% predicate is owned by the curated analogy/fewshot/blankwall reasoning tests, which
% TEACH it at runtime; preloading base capital facts pollutes that machinery. So
% "capital of <country>" remains an honest, teachable gap for now.
%
% Members are single lowercase tokens (matching the canonicalized turn). Loaded
% KB_BASE and filtered from the user-fact count (is_internal_pred), so they are
% base substrate, never counted as facts the user taught.

category_member(color, blue).
category_member(color, black).
category_member(color, brown).
category_member(color, red).
category_member(color, orange).
category_member(color, yellow).
category_member(color, green).
category_member(color, purple).
category_member(color, pink).
category_member(color, white).
category_member(color, grey).
category_member(color, gold).
category_member(color, silver).
category_member(color, violet).
category_member(color, indigo).

