% gen240 (LLMSCORE): two-line rhyming poems as KB knowledge, one per concept.
% The C assembler only selects by topic word; teaching a new couplet extends it.
couplet(ai, "Silicon minds trace patterns in the night; human questions teach their borrowed light.").
couplet(rain, "Grey is the sky and the rain won't cease; the dripping afternoon hums soft with peace.").
couplet(rainy, "Grey is the sky and the rain won't cease; the dripping afternoon hums soft with peace.").
couplet(afternoon, "Grey is the sky and the rain won't cease; the dripping afternoon hums soft with peace.").
couplet(ocean, "The ocean rolls in silver and in foam; it sings the oldest song of going home.").
couplet(moon, "The pale moon climbs and spills its quiet light; it lays a silver road across the night.").
couplet(moonlight, "Moonlight trembles where the dark waves gleam; water holds the sky as if in dream.").
couplet(water, "Moonlight trembles where the dark waves gleam; water holds the sky as if in dream.").
couplet(library, "The quiet library keeps the dust of light; its pages bloom like lanterns in the night.").
% gen241 (LLMSCORE-check): more couplet themes the bench asked for. Same engine.
couplet(sea, "The sea rolls in with silver and with foam; it sings the oldest song of going home.").
couplet(lighthouse, "Alone it stands where wind and grey waves roam; a single faithful light to guide ships home.").
couplet(storm, "The storm may roar and fling the grey waves wide; the steady beam keeps watch through wind and tide.").
couplet(robot, "A robot meets the rain for the very first time; each cold bright drop a small uncharted rhyme.").
couplet(programmer, "A weary coder sips the dark roast deep; the bugs retreat, the passing tests they keep.").
couplet(coffee, "Dark in the cup and bitter to the brim; one quiet sip and dawn no longer dim.").
couplet(coder, "A weary coder sips the dark roast deep; the bugs retreat, the passing tests they keep.").
couplet(cat, "The cat curls small against the failing light; it keeps one slow green eye upon the night.").
couplet(star, "A single star pricks through the dusk's last glow; old light still travelling from long ago.").
couplet(snow, "The snow comes down and hushes all the street; it lays a quiet blanket, cold and sweet.").
couplet(spring, "The first green shoot pushes through cold black ground; in silence all the waking world is found.").
couplet(autumn, "Autumn leaves fall over letters left unread; forgotten words sleep softly in their bed.").

