% gen241 (LLMSCORE-check): roleplay scenario advice as ordered KB steps. "As a store
% manager, what would you do?" -> a measured, grounded answer. The C prefaces an honest
% "I'm not really a manager, but" and lists the steps; adding a scenario is just facts.
scenario_step(refund, 1, "Stay calm and listen to the whole complaint first").
scenario_step(refund, 2, "Explain politely that a receipt from another store can't be refunded through our system").
scenario_step(refund, 3, "Check whether the item was actually bought here before deciding anything").
scenario_step(refund, 4, "Offer a fair alternative -- an exchange or store credit if policy allows, or directions to the right store").
scenario_step(refund, 5, "Keep the tone respectful so the customer leaves feeling treated fairly").
scenario_step(complaint, 1, "Listen fully and acknowledge the customer's frustration before responding").
scenario_step(complaint, 2, "Apologise for the trouble without admitting fault you can't verify").
scenario_step(complaint, 3, "Ask clear questions to understand exactly what went wrong").
scenario_step(complaint, 4, "Offer a concrete remedy within your policy, or escalate to someone who can").
scenario_step(complaint, 5, "Follow up to confirm the issue was actually resolved").

