% gen311 (KB-first morphology): person-indexed verb forms + pro-drop declaration.
% The translate composer emits the conjugated form for a subject+verb and, where
% pro_drop holds, drops the subject: "I need help" -> "Necesito ayuda". Grow this
% table via autolearn (conj_es/pro_drop are whitelisted), never a C conjugator.
pro_drop(es).
conj_es(need, i, necesito).
% negation marker: "I don't understand" -> (drop I) + no + entiendo = "No entiendo".
negation_es(don't, no).
conj_es(understand, i, entiendo).
% French keeps the subject but elides it before a vowel (elide_fr(je, j') in
% grammar.p0); the progressive aux is dropped (aux_progressive/1). "I am learning
% French" -> "j'apprends français" from conj_fr + tr_fr(french) + those rules.
conj_fr(learning, i, apprends).
process_step(bread_rise, 3, "Warmth and time let fermentation continue, so the bubbles expand").
process_step(bread_rise, 4, "During baking, the gas expands further and the crumb sets into a risen loaf").

